{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "lxxe:proverbs.5",
    "translationId": "lxxe",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 5,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 5 in Brenton's English Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.5.1",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:1",
      "text": "My son, attend to my wisdom, and apply thine ear to my words;",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.5.2",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:2",
      "text": "that thou mayest keep good understanding, and the discretion of my lips gives thee a charge. Give no heed to a worthless woman;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.5.3",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:3",
      "text": "for honey drops from the lips of a harlot, who for a season pleases thy palate:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.5.4",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:4",
      "text": "but afterwards thou wilt find her more bitter than gall, and sharper than a two-edged sword.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.5.5",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:5",
      "text": "For the feet of folly lead those who deal with her down to the grave with death; and her steps are not established.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.5.6",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:6",
      "text": "For she goes not upon the paths of life; but her ways are slippery, and not easily known.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.5.7",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:7",
      "text": "Now then, my son, hear me, and make not my words of none effect.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.5.8",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:8",
      "text": "Remove thy way far from her; draw not near to the doors of her house:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.5.9",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:9",
      "text": "lest thou give away thy life to others, and thy substance to the merciless:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.5.10",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:10",
      "text": "lest strangers be filled with thy strength, and thy labours come into the houses of strangers;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.5.11",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:11",
      "text": "And thou repent at last, when the flesh of thy body is consumed,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.5.12",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:12",
      "text": "and thou shalt say, How have I hated instruction, and my heart avoided reproofs!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.5.13",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:13",
      "text": "I heard not the voice of him that instructed me, and taught me, neither did I apply mine ear.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.5.14",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:14",
      "text": "I was almost in all evil in the midst of the congregation and assembly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.5.15",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:15",
      "text": "Drink waters out of thine own vessels, and out of thine own springing wells.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.5.16",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:16",
      "text": "Let not waters out of thy fountain be spilt by thee, but let thy waters go into thy streets.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.5.17",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:17",
      "text": "Let them be only thine own, and let no stranger partake with thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.5.18",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:18",
      "text": "Let thy fountain of water be truly thine own; and rejoice with the wife of thy youth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.5.19",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:19",
      "text": "Let thy loving hart and thy graceful colt company with thee, and let her be considered thine own, and be with thee at all times; for ravished with her love thou shalt be greatly increased.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.5.20",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:20",
      "text": "Be not intimate with a strange woman, neither fold thyself in the arms of a woman not thine own.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.5.21",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:21",
      "text": "For the ways of a man are before the eyes of God, and he looks on all his paths.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.5.22",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:22",
      "text": "Iniquities ensnare a man, and every one is bound in the chains of his own sins.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.5.23",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:23",
      "text": "Such a man dies with the uninstructed; and he is cast forth from the abundance of his own substance, and has perished through folly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
